{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λῐθοβόλ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> (<i>paroxytone</i>) <b>throwing stones, pelting with stones</b>: -βόλοι, οἱ, <b>stone-throwers</b>, distinguished from σφενδονῆται, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.69, compare 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 3.7.18; γυμνῆτες λ. καὶ ἀκοντισταί 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Critias” 119b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: <i>singular</i>, as winner of a contest, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “SIG” 1061.6, 19 (Samos, 2nd c.BC). \">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> -βόλος, ὁ, <b>engine for hurling stones</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 8.5.2, 4th c.BC: Moschio Tragicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus 5.208c, 2nd c.AD: Athenaeus Epigrammaticus Mech. 18.6 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; distinguished from καταπέλτης, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 20.48 \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]; also -βόλον, τό, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.1Mac.6.51, 1st c.AD: Josephus Historicus “Bellum Judaicum” 5.6.3; in full, λ. μηχαναί [prev. work] 4.9.12. \">LXX+1st c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>proparoxytone</i> λιθόβολος, ον, <i>passive</i>, <b>struck with stones, stoned</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1063 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G20639","accentedUnicode":"λιθοβόλος","shortDef":"struck with stones, stoned","mediumDef":"struck with stones, stoned","stepGloss":"struck with stones, stoned","stepTransliteration":"lithobolos","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}